entities.audiohelper/MusicalZipMover.attributes.description.ImpactSound=FMOD event to play when the zip mover reaches its node. Leave blank for no sound to occur
entities.audiohelper/MusicalZipMover.attributes.description.ReturnSound=Looping FMOD event to play while the Kevin is moving back to its home. Leave blank for no sound to occur
entities.audiohelper/MusicalZipMover.attributes.description.ResetSound=FMOD event to play when the zip mover returns to its home. Leave blank for no sound to occur
entities.audiohelper/MusicalZipMover.attributes.description.MusicParameter=Music parameter to adjust while the zip mover is activated. Leave empty to not affect music
entities.audiohelper/MusicalZipMover.attributes.description.Mode=Handles how to reset the music parameter. "Get" mode stores the previous parameter value before setting the parameter (prone to cause issues if more than one entity uses the same parameter). "Set" mode uses the value defined in the "Reset Parameter Value" field. Increment mode will add the "Parameter Value" to the parameter, then subtract it when resetting
entities.audiohelper/MusicalZipMover.attributes.description.ResetBeforeReturn=Resets the parameter once the zip mover reaches its node, instead of when it returns to its home

